law.text:
The forester shall:
Make plans for management and reforestation of forest, woodlot, and tree crop orchards;
Assist landowners of the district in marketing their forest products;
Hold meetings of county or local forest fire wardens, lookouts, guards, fire fighters, and others to instruct them in methods of forest fire prevention and extinction;
Enlist the cooperation of landowners in protection of their forests from fire, insects, and disease;
Make an annual written report of his activities to the Secretary;
Assist the State Extension Forester in carrying out the Farm Forestry Extension Program;
Assist forest landowners in formation and execution of soil conservation practices;
Keep accurate records of any forest management plan;
Assist in management of community or municipally owned forests;
Assist assessors in appraisal of woodlands; and
Advise and assist in planting food-bearing trees and shrubs for the benefit of wildlife.
